  <div class="page-content">
    <h1>Day Trading Simulator: Model Your Expected Value</h1>
    <p>
      Before risking real capital in the market, professional traders understand that trading is an exercise in applied probability. A <strong>day trading simulator</strong> isn't just about clicking buttons to buy and sell fake shares; it's about modeling the mathematical reality of your specific trading strategy.
    </p>
    <p>
      Most retail traders focus entirely on their win rate (how often they are right), completely ignoring their risk-to-reward ratio and expected value (EV). The interactive simulator below allows you to run Monte Carlo-style projections based on your trading metrics to see if your strategy naturally compounds wealth or mathematically guarantees an account blowout.
    </p>

